**Summarizing concurrency and design changes**

The refactor adds concurrency handling for key classes and implements ACID compliance with begin/commit/rollback methods where applicable, maintaining 3NF in the data model across about 30 classes. Next, rendering the design with PlantUML will help visualize and verify the architecture.
codex
Updated `LCP-UML-7/LCP-UML-7.puml` to enforce the requested safeguards while keeping exactly 30 classes. Key points:
- Added optimistic-locking fields/methods (`revision`, `beginUpdate/commitUpdate/rollbackUpdate`) and marked concurrency-sensitive classes (`Undergraduate`, `Postgraduate`, `ResearchFellow`, `CourseCurriculum`, `FinancialAidPackage`, `Transcript`, `FacultyGrant`) via the shared ThreadSafe pattern to prevent ghost writes.
- Introduced explicit transaction hooks (`begin/commit/rollbackTransaction`) on workflow coordinators (`CourseOffering`, `Enrollment`, `BillingAccount`, `TuitionInvoice`, `PaymentTransaction`) to support ACID behavior end-to-end.
- Reinforced 3NF by giving each entity a surrogate key and isolating many-to-many facts in junction classes (e.g., `Enrollment`, `GradeEntry`, `PaymentTransaction`); notes in the diagram call this out.
- Preserved inheritance, compositions, and associations from the original design; class count verified at 30.

Next steps: render the updated `.puml` to confirm visuals; if you want, I can also generate a PNG/SVG preview.
